.TH "scmi_do_xfer_with_response" 9 "scmi_do_xfer_with_response" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scmi_do_xfer_with_response \- Do one transfer and wait until the delayed response is received
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scmi_do_xfer_with_response
.BI "(const struct scmi_handle *handle "  ","
.BI "struct scmi_xfer *xfer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
Pointer to SCMI entity handle
.IP "xfer" 12
Transfer to initiate and wait for response
.SH "RETURN"
-ETIMEDOUT in case of no delayed response, if transmit error,
return corresponding error, else if all goes well, return 0.
